WEBVTT

00:08.217 --> 00:10.208
[GROWLING AND YELLING]

00:15.265 --> 00:18.302
My ear. My fucking ear.

00:18.477 --> 00:20.183
[YELLS]

00:23.732 --> 00:25.723
[GROANING]

00:27.152 --> 00:28.483
[GROWLING]

00:32.950 --> 00:34.281
You're next.

00:38.288 --> 00:40.119
RUSSELL:
Heel.

00:44.962 --> 00:46.077
Your Majesty.

00:48.757 --> 00:51.419
I said escort him,
not hunt him like an animal.

00:53.136 --> 00:54.751
He is a goddamn animal.

00:54.930 --> 00:57.262
He killed three of us,
ripped off Louie's ear.

00:58.183 --> 01:01.220
You're about to get deader,
dead-ass motherfucker.

01:01.395 --> 01:02.430
Cooter.

01:03.730 --> 01:05.595
-Back off.
-Cooter?

01:05.774 --> 01:07.310
[CHUCKUNG]

01:07.484 --> 01:09.816
-Seriously?
-Call me that again.

01:09.987 --> 01:11.477
I fucking dare you.

01:11.655 --> 01:14.488
Coot can be a little sensitive
about his name...

01:14.658 --> 01:18.196
...and the evisceration of his friends.

01:18.370 --> 01:21.282
For future reference, Coot,
I'm not a fan of improvisation.

01:21.456 --> 01:25.199
When I give you an order,
I expect it to be followed exactly.

01:25.377 --> 01:27.083
-You understand?
COOT: Mm.

01:27.254 --> 01:29.245
These wolves do your bidding?

01:29.423 --> 01:32.631
Well, unfortunately,
not as well as I'd hoped.

01:32.801 --> 01:36.009
-l'm terribly sorry, Mr. Compton.
-You're sorry?

01:37.639 --> 01:40.472
Your Majesty,
you've had me abducted by werewolves.

01:41.768 --> 01:46.353
Dragged across state lines.
They took silver to me, fed on my blood.

01:48.233 --> 01:52.602
You drank from my guest?

02:04.499 --> 02:08.162
Mr. Compton, join me at my home.

02:08.337 --> 02:10.623
I will explain everything.

02:12.841 --> 02:14.456
That was an order.

02:29.650 --> 02:31.265
[HORSE NEIGHS]

04:02.826 --> 04:04.566
LAFAYETTE:
Tara, what--?

04:04.745 --> 04:05.780
The fuck are you doing?

04:05.954 --> 04:07.945
[TARA COUGHING AND YELLING]

04:10.375 --> 04:11.410
Open your mouth.

04:11.585 --> 04:14.418
Open up your goddamn mouth.
I ain't playing. Open your mouth.

04:14.838 --> 04:16.954
-Spit it out. Spit it out.
-What are you doing?

04:17.132 --> 04:19.293
-Spit it out. Saving her life.
LETTlE MAE: Sweet Jesus.

04:19.468 --> 04:23.177
You too busy praising Jesus to realize
your daughter trying to move in with him.

04:23.346 --> 04:26.008
Tara Mae, no.
You can go to hell for this, baby.

04:26.183 --> 04:29.095
-Please, Lord, forgive her.
-Will you move the fuck back?

04:29.269 --> 04:33.262
Get out of the way. With a mother like you,
it's a miracle she ain't tried this years ago.

04:33.440 --> 04:35.021
-Where you taking her?
-Hospital.

04:35.192 --> 04:37.433
-No. Let me go.
-l'm going with you.

04:37.611 --> 04:40.023
You failed this girl for the last time,
you hear me?

04:40.197 --> 04:42.438
Now get the fuck up out my way.

04:42.616 --> 04:44.447
[TARA SOBBING]

04:49.039 --> 04:50.995
SOOKIE:
It stands for Operation Wen/volf...

04:51.166 --> 04:54.624
...some kind of secret Nazi commando force
from World War II.

04:54.795 --> 04:56.877
You found this branded
on a dead man's neck?

04:57.047 --> 05:00.460
Bill summoned Jessica there. He was trying
to show us who kidnapped him.

05:00.634 --> 05:02.170
Yeah, Nazi werewolves.

05:02.344 --> 05:05.381
That dead guy was strong
and fast enough to take Bill.

05:05.555 --> 05:09.173
He had to be something supernatural.
l was hoping you could tell us more.

05:09.351 --> 05:11.967
Never seen it before. Sorry.

05:12.145 --> 05:14.978
Why do | get the feeling
you're blowing me off?

05:15.732 --> 05:17.393
[SPEAKS |N SWEDISH]

05:18.068 --> 05:21.731
Let's go to the ladies' room
and stare at ourselves in the mirror.

05:23.949 --> 05:26.361
Here's what I know about werewolves:

05:26.535 --> 05:29.527
There's a reason their existence
has remained a myth to humans...

05:29.704 --> 05:31.080
...for thousands of years.

05:31.706 --> 05:36.075
They're territorial, vicious,
pathologically secretive.

05:36.253 --> 05:38.369
Boy, does that sound familiar.

05:38.547 --> 05:40.959
And here's what I know about you:

05:41.132 --> 05:43.714
You're so blinded by your obsession
with Bill Compton...

05:43.885 --> 05:47.377
...you're likely to run through the streets
screaming "werewolf bait"...

05:47.556 --> 05:50.138
...alerting whoever has Bill
that we're onto them...

05:50.308 --> 05:52.048
...or getting yourself killed.

05:52.227 --> 05:55.094
-You think I'm that stupid?
-No, I think you're human.

05:55.272 --> 05:57.934
-Don't underestimate me.
-Don't underestimate yourself.

05:59.442 --> 06:01.694
Your life is too valuable to throw away.

06:15.292 --> 06:17.283
JESSICA:
So, Pam...

06:17.460 --> 06:20.122
...when you're feeding on someone...

06:20.297 --> 06:22.083
...how do you not kill them?

06:22.257 --> 06:23.588
Bill didn't teach you that?

06:24.593 --> 06:27.426
Bill doesn't want me to feed on people.

06:27.596 --> 06:28.961
And now he's gone and....

06:29.139 --> 06:30.720
[PAM SIGHS]

06:31.975 --> 06:35.138
It's in the heartbeat.
You feel it in the blood.

06:35.312 --> 06:36.802
Yeah?

06:37.856 --> 06:40.768
And when it slows, you stop.

06:47.115 --> 06:49.151
Yeah, but how do you stop?

06:52.203 --> 06:55.286
I think about crying children
with soggy diapers.

06:55.457 --> 06:56.492
Also maggots.

07:00.170 --> 07:01.660
Well...

07:02.088 --> 07:07.003
...let's say that you did kill somebody
by accident.

07:08.136 --> 07:09.546
[CHUCKLES]

07:09.763 --> 07:12.129
What would you do with the body?

07:12.307 --> 07:15.094
You have no connections
in the Were community.

07:15.268 --> 07:18.931
They're not gonna answer your questions.
They don't want you to know they exist.

07:19.105 --> 07:22.723
Bill's out there somewhere in danger.

07:22.901 --> 07:25.688
l can'tjust go on with life
like that's not happening.

07:26.321 --> 07:29.404
You know that,
maybe better than anyone.

07:29.574 --> 07:32.532
-When Godric went miss--
-Bil| Compton is no Godric.

07:33.286 --> 07:36.494
But he's everything to me.

07:37.374 --> 07:38.705
[soss SOFTLY]

07:38.875 --> 07:40.661
Please don't do that.

07:42.045 --> 07:46.334
It makes me feel disturbingly human.

07:46.508 --> 07:49.170
l risked my life to help you find Godric...

07:49.344 --> 07:51.710
...and I don't expect you
to do the same for Bill...

07:51.888 --> 07:57.975
...but at the very least,
I hope you'll help me if you can.

07:59.854 --> 08:01.719
[FOOTSTEPS]

08:03.233 --> 08:07.567
Sookie, you gotta get me home
before dawn.

08:21.626 --> 08:23.833
AUGSBURG, GERMANY, 1945

08:24.004 --> 08:25.540
[GUNFIRE AND SIRENS WAILING]

08:25.714 --> 08:27.921
ERIC [IN SWEDISH]:
It's here, Godric. | feel it.

08:28.216 --> 08:29.547
GODRIC [IN SWEDISH]:
Wait.

08:29.926 --> 08:31.587
[MEN SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY NEARBY]

08:31.761 --> 08:33.262
[FIRE CRACKLING]

08:40.603 --> 08:42.104
[THUD]

08:46.192 --> 08:48.274
[WOMAN SOBBING]

08:53.867 --> 08:57.109
[IN GERMAN]
Help me. Please, help me.

08:59.456 --> 09:01.697
[IN ENGLISH]
It's going to be all right.

09:03.251 --> 09:04.787
I won't hurt you.

09:07.047 --> 09:08.912
[GROWLING]

09:11.843 --> 09:13.299
[SOLDIER YELLS]

09:19.476 --> 09:20.932
[GROWLS]

09:26.566 --> 09:28.602
[SCREAMS]

09:30.570 --> 09:32.481
[IN GERMAN]
We're on the same side, you fools.

09:33.239 --> 09:34.740
[GRUNTING]

09:45.210 --> 09:48.247
[IN GERMAN]
No, we're not.

09:48.922 --> 09:49.957
[SCREAMS]

10:21.454 --> 10:22.489
You're late.

10:23.331 --> 10:25.037
Talbot.

10:25.208 --> 10:29.451
-William Compton.
TALBOT: Welcome to Mississippi, Bill.

10:29.629 --> 10:32.462
Sorry I'm not dressed,
but we were expecting you last night.

10:32.632 --> 10:36.875
-There were complications with his escort.
-Fucking werewolves.

10:37.053 --> 10:40.216
Let's show you to your room,
get you all, uh, cleaned up, huh?

10:40.390 --> 10:42.051
My room?

10:42.225 --> 10:44.386
Your Majesty,
you promised me an explanation.

10:45.562 --> 10:49.896
And l have no intention
of letting you leave without one.

10:50.275 --> 10:52.982
| just redecorated the guest room.

10:53.153 --> 10:55.895
Wait till you see the bed, Bill.
lt's marvelous.

10:56.072 --> 10:58.905
lt once belonged
to Countess Elizabeth Bathory...

10:59.075 --> 11:01.987
...Hungary's legendary serial killer.

11:02.162 --> 11:06.030
Rumor has it
that she loved to torture virgins...

11:06.207 --> 11:08.664
...and bathe in their blood.

11:13.423 --> 11:15.038
Now, be careful of the door, Bill.

11:15.216 --> 11:18.708
It's 100 percent sterling silver
from Morocco.

11:18.887 --> 11:23.381
lt's light-tight, of course.
Bathtub's through there.

11:24.601 --> 11:28.435
And if you need anything,
anything at all...

11:28.605 --> 11:31.267
...someone will always be right outside
of your door.

11:31.441 --> 11:33.102
Just ring the little bell.

11:34.152 --> 11:37.269
You're only making matters worse
for yourself by holding me captive.

11:37.447 --> 11:39.654
Oh, no one's holding anyone captive.

11:39.824 --> 11:42.440
We're, uh-- We're conducting business.

11:42.619 --> 11:44.780
You're a guest in my home.

11:44.954 --> 11:48.287
Guests are invited.
Guests can leave of their own accord.

11:48.458 --> 11:52.076
And once you've heard my proposal,
so can you, if you choose.

11:52.253 --> 11:55.290
Enough business. Time to rest.

11:55.465 --> 11:58.252
You had the bleeds twice this week.

11:58.426 --> 11:59.962
We'll talk over dinner.

12:00.428 --> 12:03.761
So nice to meet you, Bill. Enjoy the bed.

12:12.106 --> 12:15.598
-He's a challenge.
-I think I'm gonna have to bring in the girl.

12:15.777 --> 12:16.812
Hmm.

12:17.320 --> 12:18.981
TARA:
I threw up all the pills. I'm okay.

12:19.155 --> 12:23.569
I don't need to go to the hospital.
Just pull over, please.

12:28.748 --> 12:32.286
-Bitch, you tried to kill yourself.
-I didn't plan it.

12:32.460 --> 12:36.874
| just saw the bottles,
and I thought, "Enough."

12:37.048 --> 12:40.415
-I deserve some peace.
-And I deserve to plan your fucking funeral?

12:40.593 --> 12:42.834
Spend the rest of my goddamn life
blaming myself?

12:43.012 --> 12:46.880
I'm sorry. If you take me to the hospital,
they're gonna lock me in a padded room...

12:47.058 --> 12:50.346
...pump me full of drugs,
and force me to tell them what happened.

12:50.937 --> 12:53.178
-Lordy.
-If I tell them about Eggs and Maryann...

12:53.356 --> 12:55.017
...they'll throw away the key.

12:58.569 --> 13:02.653
-Eggs would want you to live, Tara.
-Eggs doesn't want shit.

13:04.826 --> 13:06.862
Eggs is dead.

13:08.579 --> 13:12.697
The one time in my entire life
I thought I was happy...

13:12.875 --> 13:14.536
...l was a fucking zombie.

13:16.129 --> 13:19.166
What the hell is wrong with me,
Lafayette?

13:19.340 --> 13:22.457
Life ain't not having problems, Tara.

13:22.635 --> 13:25.217
It's about being able to deal
with the ones you got.

13:25.388 --> 13:28.300
-Well, obviously, I can't.
-You can and you will...

13:28.474 --> 13:32.058
...if I gotta drag your narrow ass
through this world kicking and screaming.

13:32.228 --> 13:35.891
Look, the Buddhists weren't lying
when they said life is suffering.

13:36.733 --> 13:40.976
It don't mean you get to check out early
and leave me here.

13:44.240 --> 13:45.480
What are you doing?

13:45.658 --> 13:48.650
First I'm gonna get some food in you.

13:50.580 --> 13:52.195
Second...

13:53.499 --> 13:55.410
...there's something you need to see.

14:03.217 --> 14:07.426
You want me to stay here?
| feel weird leaving you all alone.

14:07.597 --> 14:10.509
I'm a vampire, Sookie. I don't need--

14:13.186 --> 14:16.644
-I don't need a babysitter.
-Of course you don't.

14:19.067 --> 14:20.273
Be gentle with him.

14:21.611 --> 14:24.444
-And if you feel anything from Bill--
-|'|| call you.

14:30.953 --> 14:33.945
What are you doing here?
It's almost dawn.

14:36.417 --> 14:37.623
B-positive.

14:39.253 --> 14:40.914
Thought you might be hungry.

14:43.466 --> 14:46.128
Hoyt, you can't keep showing up,
leaving stuff at my door.

14:46.761 --> 14:48.672
Now, listen to me.

14:50.139 --> 14:53.631
If there's one thing that I learned
from this whole thing with my mama...

14:54.060 --> 14:57.143
...it's that I gotta take better care of you.

14:57.313 --> 15:00.100
You couldn't control yourself.
Be like if I hadn't eaten...

15:00.274 --> 15:03.311
...and people were walking around
with hamburgers on their necks.

15:03.486 --> 15:06.478
No. That's not what it's like at all.

15:06.989 --> 15:09.571
You don't know what it's like.
You never will.

15:09.951 --> 15:10.986
Biting people...

15:11.160 --> 15:14.243
...getting so mad that I do bad things
by accident, that's in my--

15:14.414 --> 15:18.077
-|t's in my nature.
-Wanna know what's in my nature?

15:19.252 --> 15:20.742
Running back to my mama...

15:20.920 --> 15:24.003
...and doing anything that she tells me
for the rest of my life.

15:25.091 --> 15:26.672
I ain't gonna do it.

15:28.678 --> 15:30.839
We can fight our natures together.

15:33.266 --> 15:35.131
It's too late.

15:38.855 --> 15:41.016
Don't say that, Jessica.

15:43.401 --> 15:44.481
[SIGHS]

15:44.694 --> 15:46.104
[SOBBING]

15:50.950 --> 15:52.531
[SOBS]

16:24.901 --> 16:26.892
So gross.

17:02.230 --> 17:04.186
Oh! God.

17:04.774 --> 17:06.890
My familyjunk.

17:07.068 --> 17:10.606
-Oh, Jesus.
-Oh, Jason. I'm sorry.

17:11.197 --> 17:14.781
It's 5 am. What are you doing
eating my chicken in the dark?

17:14.951 --> 17:17.033
I couldn't sleep.

17:19.080 --> 17:22.789
And, uh, well, | just kept thinking...

17:22.959 --> 17:27.168
...about how Gran would be doing
handstands in her grave if she saw her--

17:27.338 --> 17:29.294
Ugh. --her house like this.

17:29.465 --> 17:34.926
So I thought I'd come and clean up,
and then I got hungry.

17:36.055 --> 17:37.886
I figured you'd be with Bill.

17:39.267 --> 17:40.677
[SOBBING]

17:43.729 --> 17:44.889
What did I say?

17:52.238 --> 17:55.196
-There's werewolves?
-Yes.

17:55.616 --> 17:57.356
Holy shit.

17:57.535 --> 18:00.572
-Bigfoot? Is he real too?
-I don't know. I guess it's possible.

18:01.497 --> 18:03.783
-Santa?
-Jason, focus.

18:03.958 --> 18:07.291
-Yeah, sorry. Well, what can I do to help?
-Nothing.

18:07.461 --> 18:10.953
Apparently, that's what I'm supposed
to do too, which is totally impossible.

18:11.132 --> 18:13.373
Every sound I hear,
every time the phone rings...

18:13.551 --> 18:15.166
...every shadow, I think it's Bill.

18:15.344 --> 18:18.461
I keep expecting him to come
through the door and say:

18:18.639 --> 18:20.175
[MIMICS BILL]
"Sookie."

18:23.811 --> 18:24.926
Let me talk to Andy.

18:25.605 --> 18:27.846
I won't tell him
the whole werewolf part...

18:28.024 --> 18:30.356
...but maybe there's something
he could do to help.

18:30.526 --> 18:32.141
Andy Bellefleur?

18:32.320 --> 18:34.982
Yeah, we went through
some pretty intense shit together...

18:35.156 --> 18:37.397
...during the whole Maryann thing.

18:37.575 --> 18:38.610
What kind of shit?

18:41.203 --> 18:43.364
I don't know. I don't remember half of it.

18:43.873 --> 18:46.034
And don't even think
about reading my mind...

18:46.208 --> 18:48.790
...because I just wanna put all that
behind me.

18:49.211 --> 18:50.997
You heard about Eggs.

18:51.714 --> 18:54.046
I helped him remember things.

18:54.216 --> 18:57.549
That's why he went after Andy
and got himself killed.

18:57.720 --> 18:59.585
Yeah, that wasn't your fault, believe me.

18:59.764 --> 19:03.723
Well, tell that to Tara.
I don't think she's ever gonna forgive me.

19:03.893 --> 19:06.225
Maybe I deserve that.

19:06.729 --> 19:08.890
Well, you were just trying to help.

19:09.065 --> 19:10.680
It's the thought that counts.

19:11.901 --> 19:15.564
And, uh, Tara's tough.
She'll get through it.

19:16.906 --> 19:18.988
Sookie, you just need some sleep.

19:19.158 --> 19:21.524
Let me worry about Bill for a while.

19:24.205 --> 19:25.911
Thanks, Jason.

19:26.082 --> 19:27.697
It's just you and me now.

19:28.334 --> 19:31.417
Well, you're gonna marry Bill,
and now it's you, me and Bill.

19:45.267 --> 19:47.132
Don't move.

19:47.311 --> 19:48.426
Get out of the car.

19:50.606 --> 19:53.723
Which is it?
Don't move or get out of the car?

19:56.987 --> 19:58.488
TOMMY:
Come on.

19:59.657 --> 20:01.397
Hey, Mama.

20:02.576 --> 20:04.407
Joe Lee.

20:04.620 --> 20:05.780
[MELINDA GROANS]

20:05.955 --> 20:10.415
Quit hollering. It's too dang early.

20:12.795 --> 20:15.286
-Who the hell are you?
-Who the hell is he?

20:16.716 --> 20:19.253
My name's, uh, Sam Merlotte.

20:19.802 --> 20:23.215
TOMMY: That's the guy I told you about,
the one asking all the questions.

20:24.265 --> 20:26.927
-Found him spying outside.
-Spying? l was sleeping.

20:27.101 --> 20:29.057
All right? Put the gun down.

20:29.520 --> 20:32.307
-l'm not here to hurt nobody.
-You from Collections?

20:32.481 --> 20:34.597
Because I put that check
in the mail yesterday.

20:34.775 --> 20:38.063
Merlotte. That name's familiar.

20:38.696 --> 20:40.652
We met before?

20:40.823 --> 20:43.314
Thirty-four years ago.

20:48.456 --> 20:50.993
-Tommy, put the gun down.
-What?

20:51.375 --> 20:52.911
Put the gun down.

20:56.464 --> 20:57.920
lt's you.

20:58.340 --> 20:59.876
Yeah.

21:00.259 --> 21:01.999
It's really you.

21:02.178 --> 21:04.419
It's really who?

21:08.851 --> 21:09.931
Who is he, Mama?

21:27.328 --> 21:29.535
MAN:
Grab her, knock her out.

21:29.705 --> 21:33.118
Be back in time to watch
Let's Make a Deal.

21:36.462 --> 21:37.577
[GROWLS]

21:38.047 --> 21:39.628
TERRY:
Morning, Sook.

21:40.716 --> 21:42.627
You okay?

21:44.011 --> 21:46.218
Did you just see someone here?

21:46.597 --> 21:49.384
No. Usually when | see things
other people don't...

21:49.558 --> 21:53.551
...it's because I ain't taking my medication
andln

21:56.315 --> 21:59.899
Come on out, you big coward.
What have you done with Bill?

22:14.041 --> 22:17.158
TERRY:
Motorcycle boot. Size 10.

22:26.971 --> 22:29.132
-Now, that's just weird.
-What?

22:29.306 --> 22:30.341
Tracks end here.

22:30.516 --> 22:34.885
Which don't make a lick of sense unless
he turned himself into a bird and flew away.

22:35.062 --> 22:36.677
[CHUCKLES]

22:37.356 --> 22:39.062
Or a wolf.

22:39.233 --> 22:41.770
Yeah. Panther or coyote maybe...

22:41.944 --> 22:46.153
...but I ain't never seen no wolves
in these parts.

22:49.159 --> 22:50.695
Until now.

22:54.373 --> 22:56.284
Jesus Christi.

23:06.677 --> 23:08.759
-Tara, calm down.
-What the fuck, Lafayette?

23:08.929 --> 23:11.545
You drive me two and a half hours
to show me something...

23:11.724 --> 23:13.464
...and take me to a fucking nuthouse.

23:13.642 --> 23:16.634
How could you, Lafayette?
You can't commit me against my will.

23:16.812 --> 23:18.598
Ain't nobody fucking committing you...

23:18.772 --> 23:22.264
...but if you don't chill out quick,
somebody may change their mind.

23:27.281 --> 23:28.691
Hi, um....

23:30.159 --> 23:32.650
We're here to see
Ruby Jean Reynolds, please.

23:32.828 --> 23:34.534
Let me check.

23:37.416 --> 23:39.953
